	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />what about a 'two motion' input on the original flower?<br /><br />Something like hold B and use dpad to move the cursor to a different large 'petal', then hold A and use dpad to select the letter within the 'petal'.  Yes it'd be two button combos for one letter, but I imagine it'd still be pretty quick and work well with muscle memory.<br /><br />Then select could change case/special chars and you could even use start as a spacebar, backspace  or something  that's used frequently.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


