		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't find any of this intuitive (for console games) when compared to an on-screen keyboard where you select the letters you want.  I only see this methodology being &quot;good&quot; for something like games where chat is commonplace, which (IMO) diminishes the usefulness on non-networked consoles.<br /><br />Does anyone else feel similarly?<br /><br />Signed -- grumpy old guy who is tired of having to learn new input methods and UIs when they aren't necessarily better

		

		</td>
	</tr>
